From: Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: install libmbedcrypto compat library as a program
Upstream-PR: https://github.com/Mbed-TLS/mbedtls/pull/10777

The libmbedcrypto backward-compatibility library was installed with
install(FILES ...), which uses 0644 permissions. The resulting shared
object is therefore not executable, so packaging tools (e.g. rpm) fail
to recognise it as a shared library: no dependency information is
generated and debug symbols are not stripped from it. Install it with
install(PROGRAMS ...) instead, matching the 0755 permissions used for
ordinary shared libraries.
---
--- a/library/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-16 23:52:09.042506838 +0200
+++ b/library/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-16 23:52:09.622571855 +0200
@@ -356,7 +356,7 @@
                       libmbedcrypto.so.${MBEDTLS_CRYPTO_SOVERSION}
                       libmbedcrypto.so
             )
-            install(FILES $<TARGET_FILE:${target}>
+            install(PROGRAMS $<TARGET_FILE:${target}>
                     DESTINATION ${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR}
                     RENAME "libmbedcrypto.so.${MBEDTLS_VERSION}"
             )
